   - If `n` is divisible by any of these numbers, it is not prime.
   - If `n` is not divisible by any of these numbers, it is prime.

2. **`checkPrimeNumbers` function**:
   - This function takes an array of numbers as input.
   - It first checks if the array has exactly 5 elements. If not, it throws an error.
